{"word":"ὀλοός","slug":"ὀλοός","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ὀλοός</b></el> <el>(ὀλοός, ή, όν) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ὄλλυμι'><el>ὄλλυμι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>destroying, destructive, fatal, deadly, murderous</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Hesiod'>Hes.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <el>ὀλοὰ φρονεῖν</el> to be bent <i>on ill</i>, design <i>ill</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>:—<a href='S:Comparative'>comp.</a> <el>ὀλοώτερος</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>; <a href='S:Superlative'>Sup.</a> <el>ὀλοώτατος</el> (used as <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a>) <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>in <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> sense, <i>lost, dead</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}